Biography
 Shengda Zan was born in April 1963 in Huangjin, a village in Jiangsu Province, China. Started his career as a worker at an embroidery mill in Nantong in 1979. From 1982 to 1987, he served as a Fashion Designer and Supervisor of the said mill. In 1987, he founded the Nantong Embroidery Mill, the predecessor of Zongyi Group, by acquiring 21 old sewing machines with a $120,000 loan. Later, he ventured into plywood manufacturing business in 1992 and software distribution in 1998. Jiangsu Zongyi Company, the core company of ...
